midstSfxId.Wiki: Visual effect spawned over the course of the SpEffects duration

midstSeId.Wiki: Sound effect spawned over the course of the SpEffects duration

initSfxId.Wiki: Visual effect spawned when the SpEffect is applied

initSeId.Wiki: Sound effect spawned when the SpEffect is applied

finishSfxId.Wiki: Visual effect spawned when the SpEffects duration has elapsed

finishSeId.Wiki: Sound effect spawned when the SpEffects duration has elapsed

midstDmyId.Wiki: Dummpoly the midst visual and sound effects are spawned from

initDmyId.Wiki: Dumypoly the init visual and sound effects are spawned from

finishDmyId.Wiki: Dummypoly the finish visual and sound effects are spawned from

soulParamIdForWepEnchant.Wiki: Soul param ID for weapon enchantment. Changes the applied phantom param.

playCategory.Wiki: Stacking behavior for SpEffectVfxParam entries, if one has the same category they can't play at the same time

playPriority.Wiki: Stacking Priority for SpEffectVfxParam, if the VfxParam has a higher priority it will play over and remove the effects of the one with a lower priority

addMapAreaBlockOffset.Wiki: Migrated (add map number to SfxID → SfxID offset type)

isVisibleDeadChr.Wiki: When enabled, Vfx is displayed when the character is dead

forceDeceasedType.Wiki: A function that allows you to force the appearance of a character to be a living person or a dead person.
